{"id": "b137c4dfeb54c3e1cb1a18972d2ab9af9bc0a293", "url": "https://www.hey.com/", "title": "HEY â A delightfully fresh take on email + calendar, from 37signals", "crawl_date": "2025-07-02T18:53:46.495601+00:00", "text": "Hey everyoneâ\nIâm Jason, CEO here at 37signals.\nEmail gets a bad rap, but it shouldnât. Emailâs a treasure.\nIt feels great to get an email from someone you care about. Or a newsletter you enjoy. Or an update from a service you like. Thatâs how email used to feel all the time.\nBut things changed.\nYou started getting stuff you didnât want from people you didnât know. You lost control over who could reach you. An avalanche of automated emails cluttered everything up.\nAnd Gmail, Outlook, Yahoo, and Apple just let it happen.\nNow email feels like a chore, rather than a joy. Something you fall behind on. Something you clear out, not cherish. Rather than delight in it, you deal with it.\nAnd yet, email remains a wonder. Thanks to email, people across cultures, continents, countries, cities, and communities communicate every day. Itâs reliable. Itâs simple. It makes it easy for two humans to share their love, and for millions of people to earn a living.\nSo good news, the magicâs still there. Itâs just obscured â buried under a mess of bad habits and neglect. Some from people, some from machines, a lot from email software.\nEmail deserves a dust off. A renovation. Modernized for the way we email today.\nWith HEY, weâve done just that. Itâs a redo, a rethink, a simplified, potent reintroduction of email. A fresh start, the way it should be.\nHEY is our love letter to email and calendars, and weâre sending it to you on the Web, Mac, Windows, Linux, iOS, and Android.\n- Jason Fried\n- Co-founder & CEO"}
