{"id": "ea57324a9ab6a6f8794a746ca0eb0b4dde211094", "url": "https://pixel.google/business/", "title": "The Google phone. Built for business.", "crawl_date": "2025-07-02T18:55:12.111962+00:00", "text": "Tools to help you get the job done.\nWith powerful Google technology and more, Pixel can be customized and deployed in bulk so your team can get to work quickly.\nUnbox and get under way\nZero-touch enrollment makes it easy to deploy devices in bulk. Just open the box, turn on the phone, and access the tools and apps you need in an intuitive, easy-to-manage UI.\nAccess to the Google Play Store\nPixel devices have access to apps on the Google Play Store, offering users the ability to seamlessly integrate apps and tools for their customized needs.\nEnter the Google Ecosystem\nWith Pixel, your business can be introduced to the Google ecosystem, which can provide access to Android Enterprise, Chrome, Cloud, and more.\nMade for how you manage\nCustom-configure your device with favorite productivity apps, preset APIs, and refined mobility to support network policies.\n*Features above may require Android Enterprise.\nRevolutionize how you work.\nPixel keeps your workforce connected and productive with helpful tools like Call Notes, which can record and generate a detailed summary of your call, plus more. All while saving you time and effort by helping automate processes and accelerating workflows.\nNext-gen tech, next-gen experience\nPixel’s custom-built Google Tensor processors use artificial intelligence and machine learning capabilities to help provide enhanced experiences for your business.\nSupercharge your ideas\nChat with Gemini to start brainstorming, writing, planning, learning, and more. You can even generate images in no time — just use text, voice, or camera to get started.\nWork together across languages\nYou can use Live Translate to quickly send colleagues secure, private texts or messages in languages other than your own. No apps required.\nYour team’s built-in AI assistant\nWith Pixel, you don’t need to be at your desk to use Gemini. Simply open your phone to search across apps, summarize unread emails, find inspiration for a pitch, and more.\nTailored for how you work\nThe Gemini saved info feature helps you share your preferences for tailored responses to your business role and more. You’re in control to view, edit, or delete info any time.\nCircle, tap, and search\nCircle to Search lets you circle, highlight, scribble, or tap anything on your screen to pull up details instantly — no app-switching required.\nMore peace of mind all around.\nRecognized as highest rated for security by the Omdia Mobile Device Security Scorecard in 2024, Pixel 9 Pro helps stop threats with built-in security features, an enterprise-grade Titan M2TM security chip, and automatic updates.\nNext-gen threat protection\nHelp safeguard your OS and sensitive data with multiple layers of hardware security, including the enterprise-grade Titan M2TM security chip and Google Tensor with a built-in security core.\nSeamless security updates\nPixel becomes even more secure over time, offering from 5 to 7 years of the latest Android security features and updates to protect your business’ sensitive data.\nNo phish-y business\nHelp safeguard your phone with built-in protections that scan and notify you about potential scams in phone calls (Call Screen), texts, emails, and links.\nSeparate business from personal\nAndroid Work Profile keeps work apps and data separate from personal apps and life. Plus, with Pixel Security & Privacy Settings and Private Space, you have more control over your sensitive information.\nSecurity that’s certified\nFeel safer knowing Pixel comes with the proper security certifications. Learn more about specific certifications for Pixel devices here.\nDetect and protect\nTheft Detection Lock uses Google AI and your device’s motion sensors to detect if someone has snatched your phone, then can automatically lock your phone screen, preventing access and safeguarding confidential data.\nPower through your workday.\nPixel phones boost workforce productivity with features that optimize efficiency and batteries that outlast the day. Adaptive Battery and Extreme Battery Saver can preserve power and help keep your team running on a single charge, with Pixel 9a lasting up to 100 hours.\nMaximize impact, minimize effort\nGemini helps your team accomplish more with less effort, streamlining tasks like crafting emails and summarizing your inbox.\nStay ahead with smarter notes\nKeep organized, informed, and ahead with the Summarize feature in the Recorder app, turning your recorded conversations and more into clear summaries.\nMore juice when you need it\nThe range of Pixel 9 devices have an all-day battery that can last over 24 hours, while adaptive battery technology uses machine learning to optimize power and ensure less-used apps aren’t draining your battery in the background.\nProductivity on a single charge\nExtreme Battery Saver helps the Pixel 9a last up to at least 100 hours, by turning off features, pausing apps, and slowing processing for more time between charges.\nKeep the workflow flowing\nPeriodic OS updates help your devices avoid last-minute updates that slow workflows and create costly downtime.\nPremium features. Great value.\nEnjoy premium features like a strong processor, high-res display, and AI assistance with your Pixel at a price that won’t break the bank.\nSupercharge your productivity and creativity\nGemini, your AI assistant from Google, helps you navigate your workday with ease. Chat with Gemini to help plan meetings, summarize your emails, search your Google apps to find needed information, and more.\nState-of-the-art technology\nTake advantage of Pixel phones’ premium technology, including an all-day battery, Smooth Display, rapid processing, and end-to-end security and protection on the range of Pixel 9 devices.\nSwitch on the go\nPixel comes with what you need, including an accessible, USB-C ® port. Just turn it on and get to work, no expensive extras necessary.\nPremium features on Pixel\nEnjoy premium features, including audio message transcriptions, hands-free quick phrases, and Live Translate.\n“Best Smartphone 2 Years in a Row.”\n(About Pixel 9 Pro and Pixel 8 series)\n“The smartest smartphone in the room.”\n(About Pixel 9, Pixel 9 Pro, Pixel 9 Pro XL )\n“Some of the best mobile camera experiences money can buy.”\n(The range of Pixel 9 phones )\n“Phone of the year.”\n(About Pixel 9 Pro XL )\n“The Pixel 9 Pro XL is still the AI phone to beat.”\n“Google’s New Pixel 9 Pro Fold Makes Me Want to Ditch My iPhone.”\nWork in a whole new way.\nWork in a whole new way.\nBuilt to put businesses and AI at the center, Pixel 9a will change how you and your team take on productivity.\n-\nGet the same highest rated security features as Pixel 9 and Pixel 9 Pro.\n-\nGemini helps you streamline tasks like crafting emails and summarizing your inbox.\n-\nHave Summarize with Gemini recap your inbox and other lengthy documents, highlighting what matters most and flagging any actions you need to take.\n-\nCircle to Search lets you circle, highlight, scribble, or tap anything on your screen to pull up details instantly — no app-switching required.\n-\nAndroid Work Profile keeps work apps and data separate from personal apps and life. Plus, with Pixel security & privacy settings and Private Space, you have more control over your sensitive information.\nA phone full of firsts.\nA phone full of firsts.\nThe sleek Pixel 9 comes with Gemini, your built-in AI assistant from Google, to deliver powerhouse performance. Your team can get things done quicker, easier, and with more confidence than ever.\n-\nChat with Gemini to supercharge your productivity and creativity — brainstorm ideas, write notes, and more.\n-\nCustom built with Google Tensor G4, Pixel’s most powerful chip to date.\n-\nComes with 7 years of OS and security updates, and new and upgraded features with Pixel Drops.\n-\nBuilt to last by handling everyday drops, spills, and dust with a scratch and damage-resistant display.\nAll pro. Pure magic.\nAll pro. Pure magic.\nGive your business the ultimate Pro experience with the most sophisticated, stunning, and capable Pixel that Google has to offer, available in two sizes.\n-\nChat with Gemini to supercharge ideas, summarize unread messages in Gmail, get answers, and more.\n-\nLike Pixel 9, comes with Google Tensor G4 and 7 years of OS and security updates.\n-\nPixel 9 Pro’s all-day battery can charge to 55% in about 30 minutes, while Pixel 9 Pro XL charges to 70% in the same time.\n-\nGet 16 GB of RAM for the fastest performance on a Pixel.\n-\nImmerse yourself in a brilliant and bright Super Actua display.\nAn epic display of Google AI.\nAn epic display of Google AI.\nIt’s engineered by Google and brings you the best of Google AI first. With the largest display on a phone, you can multitask in Split Screen and enjoy immersive entertainment. Snap brilliant selfies with the powerful rear camera, and use tabletop mode for hands-free pics.\nInnovation at your fingertips.\nInnovation at your fingertips.\nWith an 11-inch screen, Pixel Tablet offers more screen space and versatility for immersive experiences, perfect for multitasking or video calling with Google Meet.\nGot questions? Start here first.\nHow easy is it to integrate Pixel with my current infrastructure?\nVery easy. With Android Enterprise, Pixel supports Android zero-touch enrollment, so you can deploy corporate-owned devices in bulk without having to manually set up each one. Just open the box and Pixel is ready to go with everything you need.\nIs it secure to use Pixel for my business?\nWith Pixel phones, you’ll have end-to-end security designed by Google to help give you and your business peace of mind. The range of Pixel 9 devices and Pixel Tablet offer multi-layer hardware security, including the Titan M2TM security chip, anti-phishing and anti-malware protection, automatic Android security updates from 5 to 7 years, and more.\nWhy should I switch to Pixel for my business?\nPixel is designed with the tools and technology to support your business needs across hardware, software, and built-in Google AI. It offers advanced security features, including security updates from 5 to 7 years depending on device, as well as automatic OS updates for at least 3 years. Pixel also comes with software to help you and your employees to perform more efficiently. And, you can easily integrate and manage it to ensure workflow is up to your standards at all times. Additionally, Pixel is part of the Android Enterprise Recommended program, meaning it has been verified by Google to meet enterprise-grade requirements for performance, consistency, and security updates.\nI have a lot of employees. How can I manage all the devices?\nWith Android Enterprise, it’s easy to scale and support your mobile fleet. Standardized features let you manage devices seamlessly. Consistently every time. No matter how many you deploy.\nHow do I use the Gemini Mobile App on my Pixel?\nTo get started:\n-\nSet up your Google Workspace account with enabled access to the Gemini Mobile App.\n-\nMake sure Gemini is set as your phone’s default assist app.\n-\nLong press the power button or open the Gemini Mobile App and start a conversation through typing, your voice, or images.\n-\nFor more details, visit here.\nCan a Pixel phone keep up with my employees and productivity?\nPixel phones are thoughtfully engineered to be lightweight and portable for easy handling. An adaptive battery learns your favorite apps and reduces power to the ones you rarely use. This limits background battery usage and helps your phone last up to 24 hours. Also, regular security updates help keep the phone current and secure, while Pixel Drops add new functionality over time.\nWhat helpful features do Pixel phones come with?\nPixel is extremely easy to use because it comes with features that are designed to help. Your Pixel lets you find answers easily and quickly just by asking. When it comes to your favorite services like Gmail, Meet, and support for your favorite third party apps it’s all already integrated right in. Plus, Call Screen will help you screen unknown callers, robocalls, and spam calls, so you can focus on your work while minimizing interruption.\nWhich Google Pixel phones have 5G?\nThese Google Pixel phones are built to support 5G that will supercharge the helpfulness of Google with an extra boost of speed (excludes Pixel Tablet):\n-\nPixel 9a\n-\nPixel 9\n-\nPixel 9 Pro\n-\nPixel 9 Pro XL\n-\nPixel 9 Pro Fold\nShow more\nShow less\nWhere to buy.\nReach out to Google Phone enterprise sales experts or resellers to find out which Pixel is available for your organization.\n-\n1\nAvailable on select devices, languages, and countries. Works with compatible accounts and some features may not be available based on corporate account settings. Internet connection required. Check responses for accuracy.\n-\n2\nBased on third-party global research firm report. Evaluation considered features that may not be available in all countries. See goo.gle/mobilesecurity for more information.\n-\n3\nRequires a 5G data plan (sold separately). 5G service not available on all carrier networks or in all areas. Contact carrier for details. 5G service, speed and performance depend on many factors, including carrier network capabilities and signal strength. Actual results may vary. Some features not available in all areas. Data rates may apply. See g.co/pixel/networkinfo for info.\n-\n4\nWorks on calls at least 30 seconds long. Not available in all languages or countries. Requires compatible Pixel phone. See here for more details.\n-\n5\nResults may be different. Image Generation available in select languages and countries.\n-\n6\nNot available in all languages or countries. Not available on all media or apps. See g.co/pixel/live_translate for more information. Translation may not be instantaneous.\n-\n7\nFeatures may differ depending on subscription, and may not be available based on corporate account settings. Compatible accounts required. Google Workspace extension must be enabled. Results and country availability may vary. Check responses for accuracy.\n-\n9\nRequires internet connection and compatible devices, apps, and surfaces. Results may vary depending on visual matches.\n-\n10\nPixel 9a / Pixel 9 / Pixel 9 Pro / Pixel 9 Pro XL / Pixel 9 Pro Fold: Pixel updates for 7 years from when the device first became available on the Google Store in the US. See g.co/pixel/updates for details.\nPixel Tablet: Pixel Android version updates for at least 3 years from when the device first became available on the Google Store in the US. See g.co/pixeltablet/updates for details.\n-\n11\nPixel 9a / Pixel 9 / Pixel 9 Pro / Pixel 9 Pro XL / Pixel 9 Pro Fold: Pixel updates for 7 years from when the device first became available on the Google Store in the US. See g.co/pixel/updates for details.\nPixel Tablet: Android security updates for at least 5 years from when the device first became available on the Google Store in the US. See g.co/pixeltablet/updates for details.\n-\n12\nCompared to earlier Pixel phones.\n-\n13\nNot available in all languages or countries. US only. English only. Call Screen may not detect all robocalls and spam calls. For more information, see g.co/help/callscreen.\n-\n14\nFeatures may require Android Enterprise.\n-\n15\nCommon Criteria certification for hardware and cryptographic library (CC PP0084 EAL4+, AVA_VAN.5 and ALC_DVS.2). See g.co/pixel/certifications for details.\n-\n16\nTheft Detection Lock, Offline Device Lock and Remote Lock requires Android 10+ and an internet connection. Android Go devices are not supported. Support may vary based on your device model. The user must be using the phone while it is unlocked.\n-\n17\nPixel 9a: For “over 24 hours”: Estimated battery life based on testing using a median Pixel user battery usage profile across a mix of talk, data, standby, and use of other features. Battery testing conducted on a major US carrier network in California in late 2024 on pre-production hardware and software using default settings. Tests began with phones fully charged. Battery life depends upon many factors and usage of certain features will decrease battery life. Actual battery life may be lower. For “Up to 100 hours”: Estimated battery life based on testing using a median Pixel user battery usage profile across a mix of talk, data, standby, and use of limited other features that are default in Extreme Battery Saver mode (which disables various features including 5G connectivity). Battery testing conducted on a major US carrier network. Battery testing conducted in California in mid 2024 on pre-production hardware and software using default settings, except that Extreme Battery Saver mode was enabled. Tests began with phone fully charged. Battery life depends upon many factors and usage of certain features will decrease battery life. Actual battery life may be lower. Over time, Pixel software will manage battery performance to help maintain battery health as your battery ages. See g.co/pixel/batteryhealth for details\nPixel 9 / Pixel 9 Pro / Pixel 9 Pro XL: For “over 24 hours”: Estimated battery life based on testing using a median Pixel user battery usage profile across a mix of talk, data, standby, and use of other features. For “Up to 100 hours”: Estimated battery life based on testing using a median Pixel user battery usage profile across a mix of talk, data, standby, and use of limited other features that are default in Extreme Battery Saver mode (which disables various features including 5G connectivity). For both claims: Battery testing conducted on a major US carrier network in California in early 2024 on pre-production hardware and software using default settings, except that, for the “up to 100 hours” claim only, Extreme Battery Saver mode was enabled. Tests began with phones fully charged. Battery life depends upon many factors and usage of certain features will decrease battery life. Actual battery life may be lower.\nPixel 9 Fold: For “over 24 hours”: Estimated battery life based on testing using a median Pixel user battery usage profile across a mix of talk, data, standby, and use of other features. For “Up to 72 hours”: Estimated battery life based on testing using a median Pixel user battery usage profile across a mix of talk, data, standby, and use of limited other features that are default in Extreme Battery Saver mode (which disables various features including 5G connectivity). For both claims: Battery testing based on mix of inner and outer screen use and conducted on a major US carrier network in California in early 2024 on pre-production hardware and software using default settings, except that, for the “up to 72 hours” claim only, Extreme Battery Saver mode was enabled. Tests began with phones fully charged. Battery life depends upon many factors and usage of certain features will decrease battery life. Actual battery life may be lower.\n-\n18\nGoogle Assistant and some related features are not available in all languages. See g.co/assistant/languages for updates to language availability.\n-\n19\nFeatures may differ depending on subscription and results may vary. Some extensions require setup. Country availability may vary. Check responses for accuracy.\n-\n20\nSmooth Display is not available for all apps or content.\n-\n21\nUSB-Type C ® and USB-C ® are trademarks of USB Implementers Forum.\n-\n22\nCompared to earlier Pixel phones.\n-\n23\nSee g.co/pixel/updates for details on when your Pixel is eligible to receive Pixel Drops. Availability of some Pixel Drops may vary.\n-\n24\nDesigned to comply with dust and water protection rating IP68 under IEC standard 60529 when each device leaves the factory but the device is not water or dust proof. The accessories are not water or dust resistant. Water resistance and dust resistance are not permanent conditions and will diminish or be lost over time due to normal wear and tear, device repair, disassembly or damage. Phone is not drop/tumble proof and dropping your device may result in loss of water/dust resistance. Damage from drops, tumbles, and other external forces are not covered under warranty. Liquid damage voids the warranty. See g.co/pixel/water for details.\n-\n25\nPixel 9a: Up to 23 watts (wired charging). Based upon use of the Google 45W USB-C® Charger plugged into a wall outlet. Actual results may be slower. Wireless charging rate up to 7.5W with Qi-certified EPP chargers (sold separately). Actual results may be slower.\nPixel 9 / Pixel 9 Pro / Pixel 9 Pro XL: Charging speed based upon testing with device batteries drained to 1% and charged with Google 45W USB-C® Charger. Charging testing conducted by Google in early 2024 on pre-production hardware and software using default settings with the device powered on. Charging speed depends upon many factors including usage during charging, battery age, and ambient temperature. Actual charging speed may be slower.\nPixel 9 Pro Fold: Up to 21 watts (wired charging) with the Google 45W USB-C® Charger (sold separately) plugged into a wall outlet. Actual results may be slower.\n-\n26\nAmong foldable phones in markets where Pixel 9 Pro Fold is sold. Based on inner display.\n-\n27\nSplit Screen requires compatible apps.\n-\n28\nScreen has rounded corners. When measured diagonally as a rectangle, screen is 11 inches. Actual viewable area is less. Dimension may vary by configuration and manufacturing process.\n-\n29\nPixel Tablet sold separately.\n-\n30\nAmong foldable phones in the US. Measurement does not include camera bump."}
{"id": "73a2303526a513fe58f58ca4a435f1449d057d82", "url": "https://docs.github.com/en", "title": "GitHub Docs", "crawl_date": "2025-07-02T18:55:12.657715+00:00", "text": "Help for wherever you are on your GitHub journey.\nAt the heart of GitHub is an open-source version control system (VCS) called Git. Git is responsible for everything GitHub-related that happens locally on your computer.\nYou can connect to GitHub using the Secure Shell Protocol (SSH), which provides a secure channel over an unsecured network.\nYou can create a repository on GitHub to store and collaborate on your project's files, then manage the repository's name and location.\nCreate sophisticated formatting for your prose and code on GitHub with simple syntax.\nLearn about pull requests and draft pull requests on GitHub. Pull requests communicate changes to a branch in a repository. Once a pull request is opened, you can review changes with collaborators and add follow-up commits.\nKeep your account and data secure with features like two-factor authentication, SSH, and commit signature verification.\nUse GitHub Copilot to get code suggestions in your editor.\nLearn to work with your local repositories on your computer and remote repositories hosted on GitHub."}
{"id": "66d08f8dd31fedf57b9c0791633f744af70253a5", "url": "https://www.apple.com/itunes/", "title": "iTunes - Apple", "crawl_date": "2025-07-02T18:55:13.613301+00:00", "text": "Download the latest macOS for an all‑new entertainment experience. Your music, TV shows, movies, podcasts, and audiobooks will transfer automatically to the Apple Music, Apple TV, Apple Podcasts, and Apple Books apps where you’ll still have access to your favorite iTunes features, including purchases, rentals, and imports.\nThe latest entertainment apps now come installed with the latest macOS. Upgrade today to get your favorite music, movies, TV shows, and podcasts. You can join Apple Music and stream — or download and play offline — millions of songs, ad‑free.\nDownload the latest version from the Microsoft Store.\nThe latest entertainment apps now come installed with the latest macOS. Upgrade today to get your favorite music, movies, TV shows, and podcasts. You can join Apple Music and stream — or download and play offline — millions of songs, ad‑free.\niTunes for Windows\nHardware:\nPC with a 1GHz Intel or AMD processor with support for SSE2 and 512MB of RAM\nTo play standard-definition video from the iTunes Store, an Intel Pentium D or faster processor, 512MB of RAM, and a DirectX 9.0–compatible video card is required\nTo play 720p HD video, an iTunes LP, or iTunes Extras, a 2.0GHz Intel Core 2 Duo or faster processor, 1GB of RAM, and an Intel GMA X3000, ATI Radeon X1300, or NVIDIA GeForce 6150 or better is required\nTo play 1080p HD video, a 2.4GHz Intel Core 2 Duo or faster processor, 2GB of RAM, and an Intel GMA X4500HD, ATI Radeon HD 2400, or NVIDIA GeForce 8300 GS or better is required\nScreen resolution of 1024x768 or greater; 1280x800 or greater is required to play an iTunes LP or iTunes Extras\n16-bit sound card and speakers\nInternet connection to use Apple Music, the iTunes Store, and iTunes Extras\niTunes-compatible CD or DVD recorder to create audio CDs, MP3 CDs, or backup CDs or DVDs. Songs from the Apple Music catalog cannot be burned to a CD.\nSoftware:\nWindows 10\n64-bit editions of Windows require the iTunes 64-bit installer\n400MB of available disk space\nSome third-party visualizers may no longer be compatible with this version of iTunes. Please contact the developer for an updated visualizer that is compatible with iTunes 12.1 or later.\nApple Music, iTunes Store, and iTunes Match availability may vary by country\nApple Music trial requires sign-up and is available for new subscribers only. Plan automatically renews after trial.\nLooking for other versions?\niTunes is going places.\nVisit the iTunes Store on iOS to buy and download your favorite songs, TV shows, movies, and podcasts. You can also download the latest macOS for an all-new entertainment experience on desktop. Your library will transfer automatically to the new Apple Music app, Apple TV, and Apple Podcasts. And you’ll still have access to your favorite iTunes features, including your previous iTunes Store purchases, rentals, and imports and the ability to easily manage your library.\niTunes forever changed the way people experienced music, movies, TV shows, and podcasts. It all changes again with three all-new, dedicated apps — Apple Music, Apple TV, and Apple Podcasts — each designed from the ground up to be the best way to enjoy entertainment on your Mac. And rest assured; everything you had in your iTunes library is still accessible in each app. iCloud seamlessly syncs everything across your devices — or you can back up, restore, and sync by connecting the device directly to your Mac.\nPresenting Apple Music on Mac.\nThe Apple Music app is the ultimate music streaming experience on Mac.1 Explore a library with millions of songs, discover new artists and tracks, find the perfect playlist, download and listen offline, or enjoy all the music you’ve collected over the years. And find it all in your music library on all your devices.\nThe Apple TV app for Mac is the new home for all your favorite movies, shows, premium channels, and Apple TV+. Watch everything directly in the app or enjoy it offline, and discover the best of what’s on in the Watch Now tab. You can even pick up where you left off on any screen, across all your devices. And for the first time, 4K2 and Dolby Atmos3-supported movies are available on Mac.\nMore than 700,000 of the best entertainment, comedy, news, and sports shows are now available on your Mac with Apple Podcasts. Search for podcasts by title, topic, guest, host, content, and more. Subscribe and be notified as soon as new episodes become available. And in the Listen Now tab, you can easily pick up where you left off across all your devices.\niTunes Support can help answer your questions\nGet help with syncing, updating to a more recent version of iTunes, or with an iTunes Store purchase — and much more."}
